description:
&lt;p&gt;Bank GP&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for GPs who are interested in working in a multi-disciplinary team in the Out of Hours service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We provide medical care to patients who require urgent assessment, advice, treatment or referral during the out of hours period. This gives you the opportunity to work evenings, weekends and bank holidays, providing the flexibility to fit in with any other commitments you have.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you can answer YES to the following questions then we would love to hear from you;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have you had enough of the ever increasing administrative work as part of your routine job?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Would you rather prefer flexible working hours?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do what you are trained to do i.e. clinical work involving patient care?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fed up of your increasing indemnity costs?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tired of working long hours on your own with no support?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working hours and shifts to suit your needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;More time with patients, less administrative work;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Indemnity cover&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to the NHS pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Other benefits include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to get involved with medical leadership, governance and audits;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Formal opportunities to develop leadership skills;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to train/ supervise GP trainees;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trust wide staff benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly supportive team with strong clinical and governance leadership;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to an in house review process/ appraisals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GP Salary:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Regular day rate - £63.32&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Regular night rate - £76.37&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Weekend day rate (from 18:30 Friday - C&amp;M) - £77.07&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Weekend night rate (from Friday - C&amp;M) - £90.00&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Bank Holiday day rate - £94.98&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Bank Holiday night rate - £114.55&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If the above sounds tempting, then don’t delay, apply today! We are particularly keen to recruit for our health economy locally, with a strong emphasis on supporting our local communities with a robust team of GPs who know and understand the needs, demographics and expectations of the population we look after. You should be committed to work shifts regularly in order to maintain competencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please read the job description and person specification for further details. Please note we require at least 6 months previous experience of UK based general practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clare Frame on 0151 514 6443&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To arrange a time to speak to our Clinical Leadership Team: Dr Zahida Adam ( Governance Lead) or Professor Clare Wilkinson (Lead GP) would be delighted to speak to you.&lt;/p&gt;
